FBIS4-28756 "dreas114_l_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 Philippines Ramos Rejects Authoritarian Rule Ramos Rejects Authoritarian Rule BK1406084194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 14 Jun 94 BK1406084194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas English BFN [Text] President Ramos rejected suggestions that the Philippines should imitate other Southeast Asian countries in using authoritarian methods to promote economic growth. Ramos said that the Philippines' often chaotic democracy should not be blamed for its failure to match the rapid growth of other countries in the region. The president said that when the Philippines was placed under martial law in 1972, economy suffered badly, resulting in greater misery for ordinary Filipinos.
